	h3
		b Lemma
	p $$f(n,i)=\frac{n!}{n^i(n-i)!}$$
	p $$f(n,i)=\frac{(n-i)!\prod_{j=n-i+1}^nj}{n^i(n-i)!}$$
	p $$f(n,i)=\frac{\prod_{j=n-i+1}^nj}{n^i}$$
	p $$f(n,i)=\frac{\prod_{j=1}^i(j+n-i)}{n^i}$$
	p $$f(n,i)=\prod_{j=1}^i\frac{j+n-i}{n}$$
	p $$f(n,i)=\prod_{j=1}^i(\frac{n}{n}+\frac{j-i}{n})$$
	p $$f(n,i)=\prod_{j=1}^i(1+\frac{j-i}{n})$$
	p $$\lim_{n\rightarrow \infty }f(n,i)=\lim_{n\rightarrow \infty }\prod_{j=1}^i(1+\frac{j-i}{n})$$
	p $$\lim_{n\rightarrow \infty }f(n,i)=\prod_{j=1}^i1$$
	p $$\lim_{n\rightarrow \infty }f(n,i)=1$$
	h3
		b Defining \(e\)
	p We know that:
	p $$(a+b)^n=\sum^n_{i=0} a^i b^{n-i} \frac{n!}{i!(n-i)!}$$
	p Let's set \(b=1\)
	p $$(a+1)^n=\sum^n_{i=0} a^i \frac{n!}{i!(n-i)!}$$
	p Let's set \(a=\frac{1}{n}\)
	p $$(1+\frac{1}{n})^{n}=\sum^{n}_{i=0} \frac{1}{n^i} \frac{n!}{i!(n-i)!}$$
	p $$(1+\frac{1}{n})^{n}=\sum^{n}_{i=0} \frac{1}{i!} \frac{n!}{n^i(n-i)!}$$
	p $$\lim_{n\rightarrow \infty }(1+\frac{1}{n})^{n}=\lim_{n\rightarrow \infty }\sum^{n}_{i=0} \frac{1}{i!} \frac{n!}{n^i(n-i)!}$$
	p From the lemma above:
	p $$\lim_{n\rightarrow \infty }(1+\frac{1}{n})^{n}=\sum^{\infty }_{i=0} \frac{1}{i!}$$
	p \(e=\sum^{\infty }_{i=0} \frac{1}{i!}\)
	h3
		b Defining \(e^x\)
	p \(e=\lim_{n\rightarrow \infty }(1+\frac{1}{n})^{n}\)
	p \(e^x=\lim_{n\rightarrow \infty }(1+\frac{1}{n})^{nx}\)
	p $$e^x=\lim_{n\rightarrow \infty }\sum^{nx}_{i=0} \frac{1}{n^i} \frac{(nx)!}{i!(nx-i)!}$$
	p $$e^x=\lim_{n\rightarrow \infty }\sum^{nx}_{i=0} \frac{x^i}{i!} \frac{(nx)!}{(nx)^i(nx-i)!}$$
	p From the lemma:
	p $$e^x=\sum^{\infty }_{i=0} \frac{x^i}{i!}$$
